## Drill down — `11111111-coca-cola.jsonl`

One JSON object per line: line 1 is the run header, the rest are events keyed by `disp` (the `#` column above). Pull the FULL command/output/reasoning with jq:

```sh
jq -r 'select(.disp=="23").command' 11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # full code of step 23
jq -r 'select(.disp=="23").stdout'  11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # its output / traceback
jq -r 'select(.disp=="23").stdout | .[0:2000]' 11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # windowed when flagged large
jq -r 'select(.exit_code != null and .exit_code != 0).disp' 11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # failed steps
jq -r 'select(.command // "" | contains("invoice")).disp' 11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # steps touching X
jq -r 'select(.reasoning) | .disp + " " + .reasoning' 11111111-coca-cola.jsonl   # reasoning per step
```
